humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, 4 out of 10 assessed lymph nodes are positive for metastasis (Axillary 4/10). Based on the new rules provided, N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes. Therefore, the N stage for this patient's cancer is N1.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has 4/10 positive lymph nodes in the axillary region, which indicates that the cancer has spread to level I or II lymph nodes. This corresponds to an N1 stage based on the TNM staging system for cancer.
